rfk in the land of apartheid a ripple of hope film screening events at stanford rfk in the land of apartheid a ripple of hope film screening facebook twitter email print add to calendar using never before seen archival footage and interviews in south africa and the united states this film tells the unknown story of robert kennedy's 1966 visit to south africa during the worst years of apartheid we follow senator kennedy to the site of his famous ripple of hope speech at the university of cape town his encounter with afrikaans students and his meeting with one of the unknown giants of african history chief albert lululi president of the african national congress and nobel prize winner when wednesday february 15 2012 6 00 pm approximate duration of 2.0 hour s where bechtel conference center encina hall 616 serra street stanford map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends tags arts international performance humanities film sponsor center on democracy development and the rule of law contact 650 723 4610 albee stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 307 30771 last modified february 14 2012
